  "hasDecisionRecord": {
    "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/decision/nagaraja-cou1-accepted-2026",
    "type": "DecisionRecord",
    "actor": "https://uofa.net/synth/actor/nagaraja-credibility-team",
    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "All 13 V&V 40 credibility factors were assessed. Twelve of thirteen factors met or exceeded their required credibility levels. The single shortfall (Test conditions, achieved level 2 vs. required level 3) was accepted because the COU is explicitly scoped to the ASTM F1717 standard loading condition, making multi-condition testing unnecessary for the stated intended use. All three QoIs satisfied the pre-established quantitative acceptance criteria (percent difference <10%, E/uval <1.96). The credibility assessment team concludes that the FEA modeling framework is sufficiently credible for the stated COU. Note: this package was generated under ProfileMinimal with a pending signature workflow; the hash is present but the digital signature has not yet been applied. Signature will be appended prior to regulatory submission.",
